From: Suraj Upadhyay <usuraj35@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2020 01:12:13 +0530
Subject: ixgbe: Remove unnecessary usages of memset
Patch-mainline: v5.9-rc1
Git-commit: 7ba068d12844e8ad2615aa4c9ffbbf023c46a92c
References: jsc#SLE-13706

Replace memsets of 1 byte with simple assignment.
Issue found with checkpatch.pl

Signed-off-by: Suraj Upadhyay <usuraj35@gmail.com>
Tested-by: Andrew Bowers <andrewx.bowers@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_ethtool.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_ethtool.c
@@ -1953,8 +1953,8 @@ static void ixgbe_create_lbtest_frame(st
 	memset(skb->data, 0xFF, frame_size);
 	frame_size >>= 1;
 	memset(&skb->data[frame_size], 0xAA, frame_size / 2 - 1);
-	memset(&skb->data[frame_size + 10], 0xBE, 1);
-	memset(&skb->data[frame_size + 12], 0xAF, 1);
+	skb->data[frame_size + 10] = 0xBE;
+	skb->data[frame_size + 12] = 0xAF;
 }
 
 static bool ixgbe_check_lbtest_frame(struct ixgbe_rx_buffer *rx_buffer,
